&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;innuendo&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means an indirect or subtle reference, especially one that is disparaging or suggestive. (संकेत)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She made an &lt;strong&gt;innuendo &lt;/strong&gt;about his past, which made him uncomfortable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Insinuation&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to an indirect or covert suggestion or hint, especially of a derogatory nature. (इशारा)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;His&lt;strong&gt; insinuation&lt;/strong&gt; that I was involved in the scandal was completely baseless.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the synonym of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;innuendo&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;insinuation&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

