	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Prosperous&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to successful in material terms; flourishing financially. (समृद्ध)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The prosperous businessman expanded his company to several countries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. Prosperous.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sporadic&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;छिटपुट&lt;/span&gt;): Occurring at irregular intervals or only in a few places; scattered or isolated.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Sporadic outbreaks of the disease have been reported.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pompous&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अहंकारी&lt;/span&gt;): Affectedly and irritatingly grand, solemn, or self-important.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His pompous speech annoyed everyone at the meeting.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Narcissistic&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;आत्ममुग्ध&lt;/span&gt;): Having an excessive or erotic interest in oneself and one&amp;#39;s physical appearance.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She was so narcissistic that she spent hours looking at herself in the mirror.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Dislike&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate antonym of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Camaraderie&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Dislike&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Camaraderie&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a feeling of friendship and trust among a group of people who work together or share an experience. [(साथ काम करनेवाले लोगों के बीच) परस्पर मित्रता एवं विश्&amp;zwj;वास की भावना; सौहार्द, पारस्परिक विश्&amp;zwj;वास]
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;A spirit of &lt;strong&gt;camaraderie&lt;/strong&gt; is not always seen among people from the same fraternity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dislike&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to think that somebody/something is unpleasant. [(किसी व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति या वस्&amp;zwj;तु को) नापसंद करना]
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;I really &lt;strong&gt;dislike&lt;/strong&gt; flying.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Dislike.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of other words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friendship&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a relationship between people who are friends. (मित्रता; दोस्&amp;zwj;ती)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amity&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;friendly relations. (मैत्रीपूर्ण संबंध)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Companionship&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;the pleasant feeling of having a friendly relationship with somebody and not being alone. (साहचर्य, मैत्री, साथ)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;cool as a cucumber&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means someone who remains calm and composed, even in difficult or stressful situations. (शांत और संयमित)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Despite the argument going on around him, he stayed&lt;strong&gt; cool as a cucumber.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Calm and composed&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to someone who is not agitated or disturbed and maintains their tranquility. (शांत और संयमित)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She remained &lt;strong&gt;calm and composed &lt;/strong&gt;during the entire interview process.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct statement is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Irrespective of the chaos in the classroom, our class teacher stays&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Stays calm and composed&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaves like a vegetable &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;सब्जी की तरह व्यवहार करना&lt;/span&gt;): Refers to someone who is inactive or unresponsive.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; After the accident, he was in a coma and &lt;strong&gt;behaved like a vegetable.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scolds all the students in the classroom &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;कक्षा में सभी छात्रों को डांटना&lt;/span&gt;): Refers to reprimanding or rebuking all students.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The teacher &lt;strong&gt;scolds all the students in the classroom&lt;/strong&gt; for not completing their homework.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develops a fever&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;बुखार हो जाना&lt;/span&gt;): Refers to someone who becomes sick and has a high body temperature.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He &lt;strong&gt;develops a fever&lt;/strong&gt; whenever he gets too stressed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

