&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Shuttle&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shuttle &lt;/strong&gt;means to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;travel back and forth regularly between two points. (दो बिंदुओं के बीच नियमित रूप से आगे-पीछे यात्रा करना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;​&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The airport shuttle transports passengers from the hotel to the airport and back.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shuttle &lt;/strong&gt;can be used as a one-word substitute for &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to move or travel back and forth frequently.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The grammatical point here is the use of a verb to describe the action of moving back and forth, which is then replaced by a noun (shuttle) that represents the same action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grapple&lt;/strong&gt;: To struggle with something or someone. (&lt;/span&gt;किसी चीज़ या व्यक्ति से संघर्ष करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rupture&lt;/strong&gt;: To break or burst suddenly. (&lt;/span&gt;अचानक टूटना या फूटना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Foster&lt;/strong&gt;: To encourage or promote the development of something/someone. (किसी चीज़/किसी के विकास को प्रोत्साहित करना या बढ़ावा देना)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Dry&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;Let&amp;#39;s understand the meaning of the given word and the marked option:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Juicy(&lt;/strong&gt;adjective)&lt;strong&gt;: means&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;containing a lot of juice and is good to eat(रस से भरा हुआ; रसदार, रसीला).
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The city Nagpur is famous for its&lt;strong&gt; juicy &lt;/strong&gt;Oranges.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dry(&lt;/strong&gt;adjective): means free from liquid and any moisture. (सूखा, शुष्&amp;zwj;क)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The paint on the door is not&lt;strong&gt; dry&lt;/strong&gt; yet.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the meanings of both the given words, we are sure that the word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;dry&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is the most appropriate antonym for the given word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;juicy&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thus,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let&amp;#39;s understand the meaning of the other options :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Oily: means&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;covered in oil or containing a lot of oil. (तेल से चुपड़ा)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Dewy&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;moist with or as if with dew(ओस के साथ या मानो ओस के साथ नम)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Watery:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;containing mostly water (जिसमें पानी अधिक हो; पनीला, पानी जैसा).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct option is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;Introvert&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;introvert &lt;/strong&gt;is &lt;strong&gt;someone who is reserved and shy, who prefers to spend time alone or in small groups rather than socializing in large groups.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: Sarah is an &lt;strong&gt;introvert &lt;/strong&gt;and prefers to read books alone rather than attending parties.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2, &amp;quot;Extrovert,&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to a person who is outgoing and enjoys socializing with others.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: John is an &lt;strong&gt;extrovert &lt;/strong&gt;and loves to attend parties and meet new people.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3, &amp;quot;Chauffeur,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; refers to a person who is employed to drive a private car for someone.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: The &lt;strong&gt;chauffeur &lt;/strong&gt;was waiting outside the hotel to pick up the guests.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4, &amp;quot;Talkative,&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a person who talks a lot.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: My neighbor is very &lt;strong&gt;talkative&lt;/strong&gt;, and I always end up spending hours chatting with her.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;cactus&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cactus: &lt;/strong&gt;Adapted to hot, dry climates and characterized by their water-storing capacity and spiny, leafless stems&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cacti (plural for cactus)&lt;/strong&gt; are native to arid regions of the New World and are well known for their ability to thrive in hot and dry environments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Their adaptations for conserving water are so effective that certain species can survive in the extreme conditions of the desert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 2&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let&amp;#39;s understand the meanings of the other given options:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creeper: &lt;/strong&gt;Plants that grow along the ground or climb by means of stems that produce roots at nodes or tips.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eucalyptus:&lt;/strong&gt; Native to Australia, primarily. They are often tall, fast-growing trees, and several are known for their oil.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sugarcane:&lt;/strong&gt; Tropical grass cultivated for its stem from which sugar is refined. Most commonly grows in warm climates with sufficient rainfall.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
